%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 55fc01baa0be7b54e8ef6801bfc93ce6, type: 3}
  m_Name: DealerOne
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  PromptOneButtonDisplay: 0
  PromptTwoButtonDisplay: 1
  ButtonOneText: No Regrets
  ButtonTwoText: No Answer
  NormalDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Decided to spend the first bullet on me? I'm honoured.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Yeah, whatever. I have a question.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Why don't you have arms? You just have hands.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: "Oh\u2026"
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: To put it bluntly, I have missing limbs. It's a slow but painless progression.
      I'm aware I have human hands too.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: I'm one of the few "people" here who still possess characteristics of
      their humanity. I haven't, let's say, fully transformed
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: You seem to have no trouble playing cards with your hooves, so let's
      move on.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: It's as if you already have disdain for me, seeing that you decided
      to shoot me first. Are you already wanting to back out of the contract?
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: No. Why do you even ask?
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Why should it matter to you? I already took the contract.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: While I've stated before that for some people, death is the only thing
      they believe can bring them peace, people can still fear death.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: I've seen fear in many pairs of eyes as the rounds continue. The way
      those people's eyes stare into mine, they secretly plead for a way to back
      out of the game.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Or maybe you don't fear like them.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Although gamblers can spend hundreds, even thousands, the option to
      leave the game, the casino, is always there.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Gamblers eventually leave casinos in an act of self-preservation, even
      if they return a day later or so.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: When witnessing other people's behaviors, especially for someone in
      my position, people can still regret the choices they've made.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: After all, not everyone knows what they get themselves into until the
      things they 're about to lose are right in front of them.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Truthfully, do you regret the contract?
  ButtonOneDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Well, no one physically forced me to fill out the contract and come
      here in the first place. I made my choice willingly. Waste of a question.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: You say that, yet there's something else "aiding" your decision-making.
      Bad thoughts?
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Like an uncontrollable compulsion? Are you alluding to addictions? Wow,
      thanks for that great observation.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: It's more than that, addiction or thrill, as to why you're here.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: And what might that be?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Ask yourself that.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Yeah right.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: They grasp their arm once more before pulling out a chunk of black fur.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: They can't hold back the tears welling up in the corners of their eyes
      from the physical pain.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: This is enough.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: The creature raises their eyes from the chunk of fur on the table to
      observe their pained expression.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: I know it hurts. This isn't Poker where you have to pretend.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Just shuffle.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Very well.
  ButtonTwoDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: I'm not entertaining your pointless questions.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: You could at least have a conversation with me. It's just us two.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: I'm not obligated to say anything to you.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: I'll walk away right now if you want to investigate me like I'm some
      criminal at fault.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: "You could, but you wouldn't. I know you wouldn't. Not because of the
      contract saying you can't leave, but because you need this \"fun\" only I can
      give you.\r"
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: "Whatever you say. I'm trapped regardless.\r"
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: They grasp their arm once more before pulling out a chunk of black fur.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: They grit their teeth from the searing pain. It's not easy to rip a
      part of your body off.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: This is enough.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: The creature raises their eyes from the chunk of fur on the table to
      observe their pained expression.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: You know, you don't have to hide the fact that you're in physical pain.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Just shuffle me a new deck and get on with it.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Very well.
